		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><i>6. Mentor teenage and college-aged boys and young men </i><br />
This is a huge one even though it comes relatively later on in life. Before going on about &#8220;respect women&#8221; and so forth something needs to come before it. Boys/men need to be able to respect and appreciate their own bodies and their own feelings when it comes to sexuality. </p>
<p>Abandon the idea that a guy&#8217;s manhood is measured by how active his sex life is.</p>
<p>Abandon the idea that a guy has to be straight to be considered a man.</p>
<p>Abandon the idea that a guy has to have a specific genital configuration in to be considered a man.</p>
<p>&#8230;.etc&#8230;.</p>
<p>Then and ONLY then can we move on to intergender relations.</p>
