		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I noticed that this article recommends teaching children the correct names for their body parts.  I have heard that this is helpful and empowering for children.  But in the first section it also uses this phrase &#8220;Your booty needs a wash. Go for it.”  Booty is the not the correct term.  I think &#8220;butt&#8221; would be more accurate as it is the short form of the word buttocks.</p>
		</div><!-- end .comment-content -->

		<div class="reply">
			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/families/the-healthy-sex-talk-teaching-kids-consent-ages-1-21/?replytocom=479647#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-479647", "479647", "respond", "91043")'>Reply</a>		</div>

