		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Good read, love the detail and simplicity of practices for any parent to follow! However, as an advocate I do not teach good/bad touch as this can be confusing for victims; if &#8220;sexual abuse feels good at the time&#8221;, i prefer safe touch unsafe touch as it addresses the protection and awareness of bathing suit area, but will not confuse kid as good/bad notion may do so.</p>
